The paper proposes a method to improve the performance of spectral unmixing using deep generative models. This involves learning the statistical distribution of endmembers and using it to augment existing spectral libraries. Given that the paper deals with image analysis and machine learning techniques, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep generative models suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and multimedia (MM) analysis, which are relevant sub-categories.
